2776	2884	h	99152	1129	2017-06-06 19:16:54.216376	2022-03-08 18:24:32.096696	Near-surface permafrost	A term frequently used in climate model applications to refer to permafrost at depths close to the ground surface (typically down to 3.5 m). In modelling studies, near-surface permafrost is usually diagnosed from 20 or 30 year climate averages, which is different from the conventional definition of permafrost. Disappearance of near-surface permafrost in a location does not preclude the longer-term persistence of permafrost at greater depth. See also Active layer, Frozen ground and Thermokarst. #{g: xqIPCC2013 | h1631}\n\n#{g: xqGCW | h1619}		h2884	archived	vernacular	\N	\N
