om clouds. Most clouds, however, do not produce precipitation. In many clouds, water droplets and ice crystals are too small to overcome natural updrafts found in the atmosphere. As a result, the tiny water droplets and ice crystals remain suspended in the atmosphere as clouds. (2) The state of being precipitated from a solution. #{g: xqPhysicalGeography | h1636}\n\n#{g: xqGCW | h1619}		h3104	archived	vernacular	\N	\N
