2883	2991	h	99152	1129	2017-06-06 19:26:29.654594	2022-03-08 18:27:37.170814	Percolation	The movement of water, under hydrostatic pressure, through the interstices of a rock or soil, except the movement through large openings such as caves. #{g: xqNOAAHydrology | h1634}\n\nFlow of a liquid through an unsaturated porous medium such as snow under the action of gravity. #{g: xqIACSSnow | h1628}\n\nIn hydrologic terms, the movement of water, under hydrostatic pressure, through the interstices of a rock or soil, except the movement through large openings such as caves. #{g: xqNOAA-NWS | h1633}\n\nThe movement of a liquid such as water through the void spaces of a permeable solid such as snow or firn, the rate of movement being governed by the porosity and liquid content of the solid, the geometric attributes of the pores, including their diameter and tortuosity, and the response of the pore walls to wetting. See infiltration. #{g: xqIHPGlacierMassBalance | h1629}\n\nDownward motion of water through the soil or a snow layer. #{g: xqWMOMeteoterm | h1643}\n\n#{g: xqGCW | h1619}		h2991	archived	vernacular	\N	\N
