2128	2236	h	99152	1129	2017-06-06 18:39:35.020777	2022-03-08 18:28:50.266652	Frazil ice	Fine spicules, plates, or discoids of ice suspended in water. In rivers and lakes, frazil is formed in supercooled, turbulent water. #{g: xqNOAAHydrology | h1634}\n\nFine spicules or plates of ice in suspension in water. #{g: xqNSIDCCryosphere | h1635}\n\nFine spicules or plates of ice, suspended in water. Frazil ice formation represents the first stage of sea ice growth. The frazil crystals are usually suspended in the top few centimetres of the surface layer of the ocean and give the water an oily appearance. In the open ocean the crystals may form, or be stirred to a depth of several metres by wave-induced turbulence. #{g: xqASPECT2012 | h1621}\n\nFine spicules or plates of ice, suspended in water. #{g: xqBushuyev | h1623}\n\nFine spicules, or plates of ice, suspended in water. #{g: xqWMOSeaIce | h1644}\n\nIn hydrologic terms, fine spicules, plates, or discoids of ice suspended in water. In rivers and lakes, frazil is formed in supercooled, turbulent water. #{g: xqNOAA-NWS | h1633}\n\nSea ice terminology, meaning fine spicules or plates of ice suspended in water. #{g: xqECCCanada | h1625}\n\nAccumulation of primary ice crystals in water and/or at the bottom of a water body, formed by supercooled turbulent waters. #{g: xqWMOHydrology | h1642}\n\n1.An accumulation of frazil in a body of water. 2.The initial stage of ice formation in turbulent water. Frazil ice consists of platelets or discs roughly 1 mm in diameter. These small platelets clump together to form shuga, and eventually (if sufficient open water area exists) form pancake ice. Frazil ice may form in open water leads and around the ice margins in the Arctic, but it is most common in the Antarctic. It may also form in turbulent rivers in winter, particularly in rapids. #{g: xqAMSglossary | h1620}\n\nFine spicules or plates of ice in suspension in water. #{g: xqSPRI | h1637}\n\n#{g: xqGCW | h1619}		h2236	archived	vernacu