3872	3989	h	99152	1129	2022-03-08 18:22:11.638352	2022-04-08 03:42:33.51171	Alpine tundra	A form of tundra in which the absence of trees is due to high altitude instead of high latitude. It lies roughly between the summer isotherm of 10C and the snow line. (Also called mountain tundra.) 	\N	h3989	published	vernacular	\N	\N
