4038	4155	h	99152	1129	2022-03-08 18:22:51.204173	2022-04-08 03:42:33.51171	Ice saints	Name given by popular tradition, in a large part of Europe, to certain Saints (Mamertus, Pancras, etc.) whose feast days, in the first fortnight of May, are said to be often accompanied by a temporary lowering of temperature and sometimes by late frosts. 	\N	h4155	published	vernacular	\N	\N
