4047	4164	h	99152	1129	2022-03-08 18:22:53.288323	2022-04-08 03:42:33.51171	Ice sheet	A mass of ice and snow of considerable thickness, defined as covering an area of more than 50,000 square kilometres. 	\N	h4164	published	vernacular	\N	\N
4048	4165	h	99152	1129	2022-03-08 18:22:53.581834	2022-04-08 03:42:33.51171	Ice sheet	A dome-shaped glacier covering an area greater than 50,000 square kilometers. Greenland and Antarctica are considered ice sheets. During the glacial advances of the Pleistocene ice sheets covered large areas of North America, Europe, and Asia. Larger than an ice cap. 	\N	h4165	published	vernacular	\N	\N
