4086	4203	h	99152	1129	2022-03-08 18:22:58.457693	2022-04-08 03:42:33.51171	Drumlin	A hill shaped deposit of till. The shape of these features resembles an elongated teaspoon laying bowl down. The tapered end of the drumlin points to the direction of glacier advance. Drumlins come in assorted sizes. Lengths can range from 100 to 5,000 meters and heights can be as great as 200 meters. 	\N	h4203	published	vernacular	\N	\N
