4511	4628	h	99152	1129	2022-03-08 18:24:27.228796	2022-04-08 03:42:33.51171	Snow pillow	An instrument used to measure snow water equivalents. Snow pillows typically have flat stainless steel surface areas. The pillow below this flat surface is filled with antifreeze solution and the pressure in the pillow is related to the water-equivalent depth of the snow on the platform. One great advantage of snow pillows over a snow survey is the frequency of observations, which can be as high as twice per day. 	\N	h4628	published	vernacular	\N	\N
