4969	5086	h	99152	1129	2022-03-08 18:26:09.896316	2022-04-08 03:42:33.51171	Summer-accumulation type	A type of glacier on which the regional seasonality results in extrema of ablation rate and accumulation rate at roughly the same time. On a glacier of summer-accumulation type, mass balance remains relatively stable throughout the year. This is typical of high-altitude, low-latitude glaciers with a summer precipitation maximum. 	\N	h5086	published	vernacular	\N	\N
