5014	5131	h	99152	1129	2022-03-08 18:26:21.844497	2022-04-08 03:42:33.51171	Hail	Precipitation of small balls or pieces of ice (hailstones) with a diameter ranging from 5 to 50 millimeters (0.2 to 2.0 inches), or sometimes bigger, falling either separately or agglomerated into irregular lumps; when the diameter is less than about 5 millimeters (0.2 inch), the balls are called ice pellets. 	\N	h5131	published	vernacular	\N	\N
