6974	7091	h	99152	1129	2022-03-08 18:35:17.650861	2022-04-08 03:42:33.51171	Little ice age	(1) The period from about 1430 to 1850 AD which was characterized in Europe and North America by a markedly colder climate than the present. (2) A period during which there is a renewal of glacial growth after previous shrinkage or disappearance during the preceding milder megathermal phase. 	\N	h7091	published	vernacular	\N	\N
