6976	7093	h	99152	1129	2022-03-08 18:35:18.122608	2022-04-08 03:42:33.51171	Little ice age	A period between approximately A.D. 1550 (or perhaps as early as 1300) and 1850 in which mountain glaciers advanced in many parts of the world. The precise timing of the advances and retreats varied from region to region. Temperatures were not uniformly colder throughout this period, but rather showed marked variations on decadal timescales. 	\N	h7093	published	vernacular	\N	\N
