6992	7109	h	99152	1129	2022-03-08 18:35:23.794077	2022-04-08 03:42:33.51171	Deposition	(1) A process by which gases are deposited as a solid without first forming as a liquid (inverse sublimation). Surface hoar (SH) growth at the surface of the snowpack as well as recrystallization of snow within the snowpack (FC, DH) result from deposition of water vapour on ice. (2) The process by which snow is deposited on the ground either with or without wind action. As a result, stationary snow deposits such as snow dunes, snowdrifts, or the snow cover itself may form. 	\N	h7109	published	vernacular	\N	\N
