7681	7798	h	99152	1129	2022-03-08 18:39:50.235552	2022-04-08 03:42:33.51171	Ice content	The amount of ice contained in frozen or partially frozen soil or rock 	\N	h7798	published	vernacular	\N	\N
7682	7799	h	99152	1129	2022-03-08 18:39:50.475274	2022-04-08 03:42:33.51171	Ice content	The amount of Ice contained in frozen or partially frozen soil or rock. Ice Content is normally expressed in one of two ways: on a dry-weight basis (gravimetric), as the ratio of the mass of the Ice in a sample to the mass of the dry sample, expressed as a percentage, or on a volume basis (volumetric), as the ratio of the volume of Ice in a sample to the volume of the whole sample, expressed as a fraction. The volumetric Ice Content cannot exceed unity whereas the gravimetric Ice Content can greatly exceed 100%. 	\N	h7799	published	vernacular	\N	\N
