7748	7865	h	99152	1129	2022-03-08 18:40:14.425213	2022-04-08 03:42:33.51171	Nilas	A thin elastic crust of ice, easily bending on waves and swell and under pressure, thrusting in apattern of interlocking 'fingers' (finger rafting). Has a matt surface and is up to 10 cm in thickness. May be subdivided into dark nilas and light nilas. 	\N	h7865	published	vernacular	\N	\N
7749	7866	h	99152	1129	2022-03-08 18:40:14.580811	2022-04-08 03:42:33.51171	Nilas	A thin, elastic crust of ice bending easily on waves and swell. Nilas has a matte surface and is up to 4 in (- 10 cm) thick. Under pressure it thrusts into a pattern of inter- locking fingers (see FINGER-RAFTED ICE). May be subdivided into dark nilas and light nilas. 	\N	h7866	published	vernacular	\N	\N
