7802	7919	h	99152	1129	2022-03-08 18:40:32.366628	2022-04-08 03:42:33.51171	Snow line	In general, the outer boundary of a snow-covered area. It has at least two specific applications: 1) the actual lower limit of the snow cap on high terrain at any given time; 2) the ever-changing equatorward limit of snow cover, particularly in the Northern Hemisphere winter. 	\N	h7919	published	vernacular	\N	\N
7803	7920	h	99152	1129	2022-03-08 18:40:32.684677	2022-04-08 03:42:33.51171	Snow line	Altitudinal or latitudinal limit separating zones where snow does not melt during the summer season from areas in which it does. Similar to the concept of firm limit except that it is not limited to glaciers. 	\N	h7920	published	vernacular	\N	\N
7804	7921	h	99152	1129	2022-03-08 18:40:32.90106	2022-04-08 03:42:33.51171	Snow line	The line or zone on land that separates areas in which fallen snow disappears in summer from areas in which snow remains throughout the year. The altitude of the snow line is controlled by temperature and the amount of snowfall (cf. Equilibrium line and Firn line). 	\N	h7921	published	vernacular	\N	\N
