7813	7930	h	99152	1129	2022-03-08 18:40:36.485264	2022-04-08 03:42:33.51171	Snow shower	A snow shower is a short duration of moderate snowfall. Some accumulation is possible. 	\N	h7930	published	vernacular	\N	\N
7814	7931	h	99152	1129	2022-03-08 18:40:36.635154	2022-04-08 03:42:33.51171	Snow shower	A fairly short period of snow precipitation falling from a cumuliform cloud and characterized by its rapid start and finish. 	\N	h7931	published	vernacular	\N	\N
7815	7932	h	99152	1129	2022-03-08 18:40:36.826696	2022-04-08 03:42:33.51171	Snow shower	A brief period of snowfall in which intensity can be variable and may change rapidly. A snow shower in which only light snow falls for a few minutes is typically called a snow flurry. 	\N	h7932	published	vernacular	\N	\N
7816	7933	h	99152	1129	2022-03-08 18:40:37.219584	2022-04-08 03:42:33.51171	Rush of snowmelt flood	The rate of change in time of discharge and water surface elevations during spring snowmelt. 	\N	h7933	published	vernacular	\N	\N
7817	7934	h	99152	1129	2022-03-08 18:40:37.72354	2022-04-08 03:42:33.51171	Windrow	A compact layer of ice cake and small ice cake formed as a result of repeated hummocking and rafting. In the coastal zone and near the fast ice boundary, the windrow thickness can achieve 10-20 m. In some cases it extends down to the bottom. Windrow presents a serious obstacle for shipping. 	\N	h7934	published	vernacular	\N	\N
